{{Infobox National Paralympic Committee | title = Paralympics Ireland | logo = Paralympics Ireland logo.png | size = 146px | country = Ireland | code = IRL | created = 1987 | recognized = | association = EPC | headquarters = [[Dublin, Ireland]] | president = | secretary general = Liam Harbison | website = [http://paralympics.ie/ paralympics.ie] }} '''Paralympics Ireland''' (formerly known as the '''Paralympic Council of Ireland''') is the [[National Paralympic Committee]] in [[Republic of Ireland|Ireland]] for the [[Paralympic Games]] movement. It is a non-profit organisation that selects teams, and raises funds to send Irish competitors to Paralympic events organised by the [[International Paralympic Committee]] (IPC).
The organisation was established in 1987, as a Coordination Committee for the [[1988 Summer Paralympics]].<ref>[https://www.paralympic.org/news/paralympics-ireland-launched Paralympics Ireland Launched], [[International Paralympic Committee]] (IPC), January 27, 2011</ref>
