'''Team IG–Sigma Sport''' ({{UCI code|IGS}}) was a [[United Kingdom|British]] [[UCI continental]] [[cycling team]].<ref>[http://www.ucieuropetour.com/templates/UCI/UCI2/layout.asp?MenuId=MjA2Nw UCI]</ref><ref>[http://www.cyclingweekly.co.uk/news/latest/433352/sigma-sport-recruits-new-riders-and-aims-high-with-uci-licence.html Sigma Sport recruits new riders and aims high with UCI licence]</ref>

==Profile==
Team IG–Sigma Sport are sponsored by the [[IG Group]], a financial derivatives company, and [[Sigma Sport (Bike Shop)|Sigma Sport]], a bicycle and triathlon retailer. The team rode senior professional events in the United Kingdom and Europe, other than the [[Grand Tour (cycling)|Grand Tours]] and [[UCI ProTour]] races.  Sigma sports was directed by [[Matthew Stephens (cyclist)|Matthew Stephens]].

Team IG ended their backing for the team after the 2013 season, and as the team were unable to find a new co-sponsor they were continue into 2014. However Sigma Sport pledged to continue to search for a new sponsor in order to return to competition in 2015.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://roadcyclinguk.com/racing/reports/sigma-sport-vows-to-return-to-racing-in-2015-after-failing-to-secure-joint-title-sponsor-for-next-season.html |title=Sigma Sport vows to return to racing in 2015 after failing to secure joint title sponsor for next season |last1=John |first1=Timothy |date= |website=Roadcycling UK |accessdate=21 November 2013}}</ref>

