{{Infobox sports league | title = Tunisian Women's Basketball Cup | current_season = | logo = | pixels = | caption = | sport = Basketball | founded = 1966 | fame = | motto = | teams = | country = {{flagicon|Tunisia}} [[Tunisia]] | continent = [[FIBA Africa]] ([[Africa]]) | champion = [[Club Sportif de la Police de la Circulation|CSP Circulation]] 4th Cup (2017) | most_champs = [[Zitouna Sports (basketball)|Zitouna Sports]] 13 Cups | qualification = | folded = | website = http://ftbb.org.tn/ | singles = | ceo = | TV = }}
The '''Tunisian Women's Basketball Cup''' or in ([[Arabic language]] : كاس تونس لكرة السلة للسيدات ) is a [[Women|women's]] club basketball competition in [[Tunisia]]. The competition was created in [[1966 in sports|1966]] ruled and managed by the [[Tunisian Basketball Federation]], and since it was held every single year. The dominant Club is [[Zitouna Sports (basketball)|Zitouna Sports]] from [[Tunis]] with a total of 13 Cups as a record followed by [[Stade Tunisien (basketball)|Stade Tunisien]] Also from [[Tunis]] with 9 Cups, and third rank is [[CS Sfaxien Women's Basketball|CS Sfaxien]] from [[Sfax]] with 7 Cups.<ref>[http://ftbb.org.tn/la-competition/coupe-de-tunisie-seniors-filles/ Tunisian Women's Cup INFO]</ref>
